Brief Overview ðŸŒŸ
Set your foot into AWS EC2 by hosting your very own WordPress website. You'll get familiar with launching EC2 instances, setting up a web server, and integrating it with RDS to hold your WordPress database.

Tools and Applications used ðŸ› ï¸
â€¢	AWS EC2: For running the WordPress server.
â€¢	AWS RDS: To set up a database for WordPress.
The Play-by-Play Guide ðŸ“š

Step 1: EC2 Setup ðŸ–¥ï¸
â€¢	Open AWS Console: Navigate to Services -> EC2.
â€¢	Launch New Instance: Hit that 'Launch Instance' button.
â€¢	Select OS: Choose an Amazon Linux 2 AMI.
â€¢	Instance Type: Go for t2.micro; it's eligible for the Free Tier.
â€¢	Review and Launch: Click 'Review and Launch', then 'Launch'.

-- AWS CLI to launch EC2 --

CSS  code
( aws ec2 run-instances --image-id ami-abcdef123 --count 1 --instance-type t2.micro --key-name YourKeyName  )

Step 2: Install Apache and PHP ðŸ› ï¸
â€¢	SSH into EC2: Open your terminal and SSH into your instance.
Java Code

( ssh -i "YourKeyName.pem" ec2-user@your-EC2-public-IP )

â€¢	Update Packages: Run sudo yum update.
â€¢	Install Apache: sudo yum install httpd.
â€¢	Start Apache: sudo systemctl start httpd.
â€¢	Install PHP: sudo amazon-linux-extras install -y php7.2.

Step 3: RDS Setup ðŸ“š
â€¢	Open AWS Console: Services -> RDS.
â€¢	Launch DB: Click 'Create database'.
â€¢	Choose Engine: Select MySQL.
â€¢	Configure: Choose Free tier, then set username and password.
â€¢	Create: Hit that 'Create database' button.
-- AWS CLI for RDS --

CSS Code 
 ( aws rds create-db-instance --db-name YourDBName --db-instance-identifier YourInstanceIdentifier --engine MySQL --master-username YourMasterUsername --master-user-password YourPassword --allocated-storage 20 --db-instance-class db.t2.micro --vpc-security-group-ids your-security-group-id )

Step 4: Connect EC2 and RDS ðŸ”—
â€¢	Modify wp-config: SSH into EC2, navigate to WordPress folder, and edit wp-config.php.

SQL Code Insert 
define('DB_NAME', 'YourDBName'); 
define('DB_USER', 'YourMasterUsername'); 
define('DB_PASSWORD', 'YourPassword');
 define('DB_HOST', 'YourRDSHost'); 

Step 5: Test WordPress ðŸŽ‰
â€¢	Access WordPress: Open your web browser and go to http://your-EC2-public-IP/wordpress.
â€¢	Follow Setup: Complete the WordPress installation wizard.
